Thought: In our case, we know the malicious URL "https://dj01161621.bravesand-e1ccd718.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/" was clicked and later an email event removed the malicious part from the email. The EmailUrlInfo table stores the URLs found in emails keyed by the NetworkMessageId. The EmailPostDeliveryEvents table has post-delivery remediation events and includes the email recipient address using the same NetworkMessageId. To determine the recipient email address, we can first locate the record from EmailUrlInfo that has the malicious URL, retrieve its NetworkMessageId, and then join with EmailPostDeliveryEvents to get the RecipientEmailAddress. I will use a join query to perform this correlation.
Action: execute[SELECT epe.RecipientEmailAddress
FROM EmailUrlInfo AS ezi
JOIN EmailPostDeliveryEvents AS epe ON ezi.NetworkMessageId = epe.NetworkMessageId
WHERE ezi.Url = 'https://dj01161621.bravesand-e1ccd718.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/';
]

Thought: I'll now search for records in the EmailUrlInfo table that have the malicious URL "login.micro.demo.antoinetest.ovh" to see if any email contained it. This should provide the NetworkMessageId that we can then use to join with EmailEvents for the recipient email.
Action: execute[
SELECT *
FROM EmailUrlInfo
WHERE Url = 'login.micro.demo.antoinetest.ovh';
]

Thought: I'll search in the AlertEvidence table for any evidence that mentions the URL "login.micro.demo.antoinetest.ovh". This table may contain correlated evidence referenced by the SecurityAlert and SecurityIncident records that can indicate the email recipient.
Action: execute[
SELECT *
FROM AlertEvidence
WHERE EvidenceData LIKE '%login.micro.demo.antoinetest.ovh%';
]

Thought: The AuditLogs query returned no matches, so I'll try searching for entries in AuditLogs that reference part of the suspicious URL (e.g. "bravesand") in the AdditionalDetails field which may indicate the ARM operation triggered using the URL. This might show the ResourceId we need.
Action: execute[
SELECT ResourceId, AdditionalDetails, InitiatedBy, OperationName, ActivityDateTime 
FROM AuditLogs 
WHERE AdditionalDetails LIKE '%bravesand%';
]
